<ul class="task-constraints">
<li><b>Time limit:</b> 1.00 s</li>
<li><b>Memory limit:</b> 512 MB</li>
</ul>
<input type="hidden" name="course" value="problemset">
<input type="hidden" name="task" value="1623">
There are $n$ apples with known weights. Your task is to divide the apples into two groups so that the difference between the weights of the groups is minimal.<br />
<br />
<b id="input">Input</b><br />
<br />
The first input line has an integer $n$: the number of apples.<br />
<br />
The next line has $n$ integers $p_1,p_2,\dots,p_n$: the weight of each apple.<br />
<br />
<b id="output">Output</b><br />
<br />
Print one integer: the minimum difference between the weights of the groups.<br />
<br />
<b id="constraints">Constraints</b><br />
<ul>
<li>$1 \le n \le 20$<br />
<li>$1 \le p_i \le 10^9$<br />
</ul>
<b id="example">Example</b><br />
<br />
Input:<br />
<code>5<br />
3 2 7 4 1</code><br />
<br />
Output:<br />
<code>1</code><br />
<br />
Explanation: Group 1 has weights 2, 3 and 4 (total weight 9), and group 2 has weights 1 and 7 (total weight 8).    </div>
